-- Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Celsia, Ecopetrol Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-06-14T20:23:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/colombian-stocks-celsia-pacific-rubiales-bancolombia.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the market close.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.3 percent to 13,943.74, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.7 percent to 1,665.18.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest lender,
dropped 1.1 percent to 27,200 pesos. Finance Minister Juan
Carlos Echeverry said Colombia’s economy grew 4.5 percent in the
first quarter from a year earlier, compared with the previous
estimate of 4.8 percent, in a speech in Bogota today.  Celsia SA (CELSIA)  , a Colombian electricity holding
company, gained 2.1 percent to 4,340 pesos. Celsia started
operations today at a new power plant, known as Hidromontanitas,
with generating capacity of 19.9 megawatts, according to a
regulatory  filing .  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 1.2 percent to 5,220 pesos. Crude gained the most in more
than two months in  New York  trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
